Eskom, Transnet, SAA to Create 130,000 Jobs by 2016, Business Report Says

-- B y   S t e p h e n   G u n n i o n
-- 
2011-06-29T05:23:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-29/eskom-transnet-saa-to-create-130-000-jobs-by-2016-business-report-says.html
Eskom Holdings SOC Ltd., Transnet
SOC Ltd.,  South African Airways  Ltd. and other state-owned
companies plan to create more than 130,000 jobs within the next
three to five years,  Business Report  said.  Power utility Eskom plans to create 100,000 jobs, the
Johannesburg-based newspaper said, citing Chief Commercial
Officer Dan Marokane. Ports and freight rail operator Transnet
aims to create almost 30,000 jobs, Business Report said, citing
Chief Executive Officer Brian Molefe.  South African Airways, the state-owned airline, aims to
create 1,615 jobs, the newspaper said, without citing anyone.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephen Gunnion in Johannesburg at 
 sgunnion@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alastair Reed at 
 areed12@bloomberg.net  